Resonance as Confidence

Confidence describes the reliability of a system’s internal state.

In TERA, confidence is not a probability but a stability condition:

High confidence → ACCEPT

Uncertain confidence → WAIT

Low confidence → REJECT


Thus, confidence is defined as:

\text{Confidence} = f(\text{stability of } I \cdot E \cdot \omega)

A system is confident when its evolution requires no correction.


