---

Resistance and Resilience

The TERA model distinguishes between two stability mechanisms.

Resistance

Resistance is the ability of a system to oppose change.

It corresponds to low sensitivity to perturbation:

\delta S \approx 0 \quad \text{under disturbance}

A highly resistant system minimizes immediate deviation.


---

Resilience

Resilience is the ability of a system to recover after disturbance.

It corresponds to returning to a stable trajectory:

\lim_{t \to \infty} ||C(t)|| \rightarrow \text{bounded}

Resilience allows temporary instability while preserving long-term coherence.


---

Relation to Resonance

Resistance stabilizes structure against change

Resilience stabilizes structure through change

Resonance balances both


Thus:

\text{Resonance} = \text{optimal balance of resistance and resilience}


